      "content": "Wealth redistribution is the only proven mechanism to dismantle systemic racial inequality because it directly attacks the historical accumulation of wealth that has long favored white families over Black and Brown communities. By implementing progressive taxation and universal basic income, we can reverse centuries of discriminatory policies like redlining and Jim Crow laws that artificially suppressed Black economic mobility. This approach isn't just about fairness; it is a necessary economic shock to break the cycle of poverty that disproportionately affects people of color. Ultimately, true equality requires a radical restructuring of our tax code to ensure that the most vulnerable in society, regardless of race, have the resources to thrive.",
