      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can dismantle the meritocracy argument by proving that the \"playing field is level\" myth is a lie that protects the wealthy from accountability for historical theft. Since systemic barriers like redlining and discriminatory lending have stripped Black families of generational wealth, the idea that success is solely a result of individual effort ignores the massive head start white families have. Framing meritocracy as a harmful ideology reveals how it excuses systemic injustice by blaming victims for outcomes they never had the chance to achieve. Your essay should argue that true merit requires a level playing field, which only wealth redistribution can provide.",
      "source": "target",
